01:24:27,192 --> 01:24:29,486
Louis XIII, et voila.

952
01:24:30,487 --> 01:24:32,572
Shall we let it breathe?

953
01:24:32,655 --> 01:24:38,119
It hasn't breathed in 50 years.
It's dead. Let's just drink it.

954
01:24:50,423 --> 01:24:54,386
- Health and friendship?
- Life and love.

955
01:25:03,019 --> 01:25:08,858
Douglas Coughlin,
your ship has certainly come in.

956
01:25:11,903 --> 01:25:14,406
My ship.

957
01:25:14,489 --> 01:25:18,660
My ship is going down,
and I'm going down with it.

958
01:25:18,743 --> 01:25:21,246
- How is that?
- All this is an illusion.

959
01:25:21,329 --> 01:25:25,375
I'm on my arse.
I haven't got a pot to piss in.

960
01:25:27,627 --> 01:25:29,879
A hundred grand a week. Painful.

961
01:25:31,172 --> 01:25:35,802
I should have read some of your
sacred books, young Flanagan.

962
01:25:35,885 --> 01:25:40,432
All I know about saloons is how
to pour whiskey and run my mouth off.

963
01:25:40,515 --> 01:25:44,269
I knew nothing about insurance,...

964
01:25:45,770 --> 01:25:51,317
..or sales tax, or the building code,
or labour costs.

965
01:25:51,401 --> 01:25:54,738
Or the power company,
or purchasing, or linens.

966
01:25:54,821 --> 01:25:57,532
Everyone with a hand
stuck it in my pocket.

967
01:25:57,615 --> 01:25:59,534
You must make enough to cover that.

968
01:25:59,617 --> 01:26:04,205
If I'd stuck to what I know best,
which is almost nothing.

969
01:26:05,415 --> 01:26:09,252
Instead, I put all the cash
into commodities,

970
01:26:09,336 --> 01:26:12,589
and blew the fucking lot.

971
01:26:13,840 --> 01:26:18,428
On the margin.
Buy. Cover. Buy. Cover.

972
01:26:18,511 --> 01:26:21,431
I wanted it fast.

973
01:26:24,976 --> 01:26:27,187
See the headlines.

974
01:26:27,270 --> 01:26:32,067
"Douglas Coughlin.
From bartender to billionaire."

975
01:26:38,323 --> 01:26:41,034
- Doug, take it easy.
- Relax.

976
01:26:41,117 --> 01:26:45,747
The luck is gone.
The brain is shot.

977
01:26:45,830 --> 01:26:48,333
But the liquor we still got.

978
01:26:52,212 --> 01:26:53,672
Doug?

979
01:26:55,423 --> 01:26:57,509
Doug, are you down there?

980
01:26:57,592 --> 01:27:02,806
She knows nothing about this.
She thinks I'm a fucking hero.

981
01:27:08,561 --> 01:27:12,315
My princess. My dream.

982
01:27:13,233 --> 01:27:17,737
Oh, baby, not again.
I want to go home.

983
01:27:18,321 --> 01:27:22,325
Come here. Toast Flanagan.

984
01:27:22,409 --> 01:27:27,622
To the first and last person
I ever cared about.

985
01:27:28,998 --> 01:27:30,667
To my wife.

986
01:27:30,750 --> 01:27:32,419
Doug?

987
01:27:34,546 --> 01:27:37,257
Wake up. I want to go home.

988
01:27:59,654 --> 01:28:02,782
You're the only person
in the world Doug respects.

989
01:28:05,910 --> 01:28:08,204
We were a good team once.

990
01:28:09,748 --> 01:28:14,127
Walk me to my apartment.
I hate going into that place alone.

991
01:28:18,214 --> 01:28:21,343
- I'd better check on Doug.
- Please.

992
01:28:22,093 --> 01:28:26,056
I want to talk about Doug,
about his problems.

993
01:29:03,802 --> 01:29:08,598
Doug says you're incredible
with women. A real lady-killer.

994
01:29:09,641 --> 01:29:14,688
- Is that what he says?
- What's your secret weapon?

995
01:29:16,189 --> 01:29:19,734
Well, what you see is what you get.

996
01:29:38,628 --> 01:29:41,339
- Hold it.
- What did you do that for?

997
01:29:46,011 --> 01:29:49,514
I can't make it
with my best friend's old lady.

998
01:29:51,266 --> 01:29:55,770
Am I supposed to live with the same
man day in and day out forever?

999
01:29:55,854 --> 01:30:00,442
- And have no one else in my life?
- Yes. It's called marriage.

1000
01:30:00,525 --> 01:30:04,612
You want this as much as I do.
That's why you're up here.

1001
01:30:04,696 --> 01:30:08,450
But you can't do it now, can you?
You're scared.

1002
01:30:11,119 --> 01:30:13,038
I don't know what I'm doing.

1003
01:30:13,121 --> 01:30:15,248
You're just scared!

1004
01:30:39,439 --> 01:30:40,899
Hey, Doug.

1005
01:30:52,118 --> 01:30:53,995
Help me!

1006
01:30:54,079 --> 01:30:56,664
Somebody help me!

1007
01:30:56,748 --> 01:31:01,378
No! Somebody help me!

1008
01:31:13,890 --> 01:31:15,975
Is there anything you can tell me?

1009
01:31:52,387 --> 01:31:55,515
"The Lord is my shepherd.
I shall not want."

1010
01:32:35,847 --> 01:32:41,144
My dearest Brian,
A guy like me looks in the mirror,

1011
01:32:41,227 --> 01:32:44,147
he either grins,
or he starts to fade away.

1012
01:32:44,939 --> 01:32:48,485
And I haven't seen anything
to grin about in a long time.

1013
01:32:49,736 --> 01:32:52,906
This may not be
the most graceful exit,

1014
01:32:52,989 --> 01:32:55,617
but I know when the bottle's empty.

1015
01:32:55,700 --> 01:32:58,536
The only thing
I'm really going to miss

1016
01:32:58,620 --> 01:33:01,331
is the conversations we had.

1017
01:33:02,582 --> 01:33:06,753
At least I get the last word,
even if I had to mail it in.

1018
01:33:08,380 --> 01:33:13,176
Coughlin's Law: Bury the dead.
They stink up the joint.

1019
01:33:13,259 --> 01:33:16,388
As for the rest of Coughlin's Laws,
ignore them.

1020
01:33:16,471 --> 01:33:19,182
The guy was always full of shit.

1021
01:33:22,560 --> 01:33:25,063
But I guess you knew that already.

1022
01:33:49,796 --> 01:33:54,718
- Mooneys' apartment. Brian...
- I know. I'm not to let you in.

1023
01:33:54,801 --> 01:33:57,429
- If you just...
- Leave now!

1024
01:33:57,512 --> 01:34:02,017
I just want to talk to her.
I don't want to cause any trouble.

1025
01:34:02,100 --> 01:34:05,020
- Send her a letter. Out!
- Get your hands off me.

1026
01:34:05,103 --> 01:34:06,563
Out!

1027
01:34:22,412 --> 01:34:25,331
- Where's Jordan?
- In there.

1028
01:34:25,415 --> 01:34:28,126
You can't go in there.
Open the door.

1029
01:34:28,209 --> 01:34:30,295
Jordan?

1030
01:34:31,379 --> 01:34:33,590
- I must talk to you.
- What's going on?

1031
01:34:33,673 --> 01:34:36,885
There's so many things.
I don't know where to begin.

1032
01:34:36,968 --> 01:34:38,219
Doug is dead.

1033
01:34:39,012 --> 01:34:41,723
- What?
- He killed himself.

1034
01:34:43,183 --> 01:34:45,935
He was my friend,
but was too proud to let me help,

1035
01:34:46,019 --> 01:34:49,147
too proud to show how he felt
until it was too late.

1036
01:34:49,230 --> 01:34:51,232
I won't make that mistake.

1037
01:34:53,818 --> 01:34:57,572
- He pushed past me.
- I told you to keep him out of here.

1038
01:34:57,655 --> 01:34:59,824
- He got by me.
- Jordan, are you in there?

1039
01:34:59,908 --> 01:35:03,870
I've saved money
and got a loan from my uncle.

1040
01:35:03,953 --> 01:35:07,290
With hard work, I know
I can turn it into something great.

1041
01:35:07,374 --> 01:35:11,002
I know you can,
but it doesn't really matter.

1042
01:35:11,086 --> 01:35:12,462
Listen to me!

1043
01:35:12,545 --> 01:35:14,798
Get me the key.

1044
01:35:14,881 --> 01:35:16,841
I love you. I want to marry you.

1045
01:35:16,925 --> 01:35:19,844
I've loved you
from the first moment I saw you.

1046
01:35:19,928 --> 01:35:22,931
- Open the door!
- Please. Please come with me.

1047
01:35:23,973 --> 01:35:26,685
Flanagan,
get the hell out of my house!

1048
01:35:26,768 --> 01:35:30,522
Jordan, wake up. Don't you see why
he's come back? It's for the money.

1049
01:35:30,605 --> 01:35:34,442
- No, I don't want a thing from you.
- You won't get a penny.

1050
01:35:34,526 --> 01:35:37,028
- He's a loser.
- I'm not. Jordan, come with me.

1051
01:35:37,112 --> 01:35:38,321
Get him out of here.

1052
01:35:38,405 --> 01:35:40,657
Stay out of this. Please.

1053
01:35:40,740 --> 01:35:43,743
Throw him out of here! Come on!

1054
01:35:43,827 --> 01:35:46,454
- Hold it! Just hold it!
- Jordan, don't!

1055
01:35:46,538 --> 01:35:49,457
If you leave,
don't bother coming back.

1056
01:35:49,541 --> 01:35:53,336
- I'm going. I love him. I'm going.
- You're not going anywhere.

1057
01:35:53,420 --> 01:35:54,879
Stop her!

1058
01:35:55,839 --> 01:35:58,258
Get your hands off her!
She's pregnant!

1059
01:36:00,010 --> 01:36:01,678
You asshole!

1060
01:36:17,318 --> 01:36:20,447
It didn't have to be this way,
you know.

1061
01:36:30,665 --> 01:36:34,836
- You're on your own.
- That's the only way I want it.

1062
01:36:41,634 --> 01:36:45,096
A toast.
To the bride and to my nephew.

1063
01:36:45,180 --> 01:36:47,015
All the happiness.

1064
01:36:53,730 --> 01:36:57,275
When will I be loved?

1065
01:36:57,359 --> 01:36:58,818
Right now, baby.

1066
01:37:20,006 --> 01:37:22,425
You realise
we're both completely insane?

1067
01:37:22,509 --> 01:37:23,551
Yes.

1068
01:37:23,635 --> 01:37:26,721
You'll probably want to divorce me
in three weeks.

1069
01:37:26,805 --> 01:37:28,598
Probably.

1070
01:37:28,682 --> 01:37:31,685
No, you'll want to divorce me
when I'm fat and ugly.

1071
01:37:31,768 --> 01:37:33,436
Just don't get too fat.

1072
01:37:33,520 --> 01:37:38,358
I am going to be very fat,
and you are gonna love it.

1073
01:37:50,161 --> 01:37:53,456
- Brian, give us a poem.
- Yeah, come on.

1074
01:37:54,207 --> 01:37:56,918
A poem?

1075
01:38:02,340 --> 01:38:05,885
- We want a poem!
- Alright. A poem.

1076
01:38:16,521 --> 01:38:18,606
OK, a poem.

1077
01:38:20,483 --> 01:38:22,777
This poem is entitled...

1078
01:38:23,862 --> 01:38:26,781
.."Flanagan's Advice
To His Unborn Child."

1079
01:38:30,285 --> 01:38:35,707
Now, if Jordan gives birth
to a fine Irish son

1080
01:38:35,790 --> 01:38:38,960
There'll be Cocktails & Dreams
for him one day to run

1081
01:38:40,003 --> 01:38:43,340
A business that shall yield
a financial windfall

1082
01:38:43,423 --> 01:38:44,466
It better!

1083
01:38:45,300 --> 01:38:46,551
Yes.

1084
01:38:46,968 --> 01:38:50,096
To be franchised
in every suburban shopping mall

1085
01:38:50,180 --> 01:38:53,016
A dynasty! We're founding a dynasty!

1086
01:38:53,767 --> 01:38:55,226
Now.

1087
01:38:56,353 --> 01:39:00,523
If a daughter arrives
to bless our clan

1088
01:39:01,441 --> 01:39:04,069
I guess the shit
will certainly hit the fan

1089
01:39:06,863 --> 01:39:10,450
But this I shall promise to thee

1090
01:39:10,533 --> 01:39:13,328
I'll never let her marry
a guy like me

1091
01:39:14,496 --> 01:39:20,335
Still, if she's the naughtiest of
girls with the wildest of young men

1092
01:39:20,960 --> 01:39:24,005
I swear l will be the best dad I can

1093
01:39:24,089 --> 01:39:28,301
And never, ever get spooked again.

1094
01:39:32,847 --> 01:39:36,393
- I bet I can still spook you.
- No way.

1095
01:39:42,857 --> 01:39:44,943
Twins?

1096
01:39:45,944 --> 01:39:47,612
Twins?

1097
01:39:47,696 --> 01:39:49,989
Twins!

1098
01:39:51,324 --> 01:39:54,160
- Drinks are on the house.
- No! No!

1099
01:39:54,244 --> 01:39:56,746
The bar is open!
